              <h3>Bring Home<br/> To Mom</h3>
              <hr class="flared-edges"><br/>
              <p><em>Overview:</em> Bring Home To Mom is a match-making and date-planning app targeted to parents. Parents create profiles for their children, browse and filter for potential matches, plan dates while communicating with the other child's parents, and split the cost of the upcoming date so everything is prepaid.</p>
              <p><em>Technology:</em> Ruby on Rails and PostgreSQL on the back end, and a mix of JavaScript, jQuery, AJAX, and handlebars.js on the front-end to deliver a single-page experience across much of the site.  API integrations include Stripe for payments, Twilio for MMS notifications, Cloudinary for images, and Rotten Tomatoes and OMDB for local movie listings.</p>
              <p><em>Background:</em> This was my final project at Dev Bootcamp.  I conceived and pitched the idea, and led a team of four to create the feature-rich product in exactly one week. </p>
              <p><em>Creators:</em> Jonathan Berk, Sophie Garden, Tony Mai, Kevin Ceballos.  Created April 2015.</p>
