          <div class="project-details">
            <div class="vertical-center">
              <h3>#98problems</h3>
              <hr class="flared-edges"><br/>
              <p><em>Overview:</em> #98problems is a tool to organize music on Spotify using tags instead of traditional playlists. After importing their Spotify library and tagging tracks with various characteristics, users can filter their collection and generate on-the-fly playlists containing only songs matching a particular set of attributes (e.g. "workout', "mashup", instrumental"). Playlists are instantly exported to Spotify for easy listening on the go.</p>
              <p><em>Technology:</em> Ruby, Sinatra and PostgreSQL on back end.  JavaScript, jQuery & AJAX to interact with database without reloading.  Bootstrap for basic page styling.  Spotify API and OAuth 2.0 integration.</p>
              <p><em>Background:</em> This was a solo project I completed in one week at Dev Bootcamp.</p>
